\begin_layout Standard
Consider a random mixture of 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 materials with density 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \varrho_{i}\right\} _{i=1,2,\dots,n}$
\end_inset

 and eletrical conductivity 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \rho_{i}\right\} _{i=1,2,\dots,n}$
\end_inset

.
 The total mass of material 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 in the mixture is 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 Compress the mixture into a cylinder, the hight and cross-sectional area
 of which are 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $A=\pi r^{2}$
\end_inset

, respectively.
 What is the resistance of the mixture?
